description:
&lt;p&gt;The seven integrated regions of our joint enterprise will work with local systems to support and improve how care is provided to patients and communities. These regions will be supported by the corporate centre providing expertise and developing policy. The focus will be on guiding and managing the delivery of services through local integrated health systems, sustainability and transformation partnerships, and devolution areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Primary Care Programme Support (Digital), the post holder will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering an effective service supporting managers and staff across the Digital Primary Care Transformation regional team to provide an effective administrative and programme support service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as part of a matrix with NHSx, NHS Digital, local CCG, Provider Trusts, CSU’s and other Digital/Informatics delivery colleagues, providing administrative and business support to the regional Digital Primary Care Transformation team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide high quality project, service, initiative and administrative support including information and analysis, to include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First point of contact for the team, ensuring that queries are tracked, signposted and responded to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To undertake configuration management on behalf of the team; monitoring and maintaining documentation and filing structures in Office 365&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To undertake ad hoc administrative tasks and project support tasks when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Authorised signatory for travel arrangements and meeting expenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support with reporting and analysis of information to support delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work in a matrix fashion, with the wider North East and Yorkshire Regional Digital Transformation Team to ensure the directorate’s objectives are delivered regionally and locally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To maintain relationships across NHS England and NHS Improvement and its partners for increasing success in delivery of the Digital agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support an efficient, high quality and confidential programme and administrative support service to the programme so that it can meet its objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support for setting up and running stakeholder events relevant to the team’s work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preparation of agendas and minutes, taking appropriate follow-up action as required for programme related meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is a key member of the team whose overarching goal is to promote and support the effective use of data, information, knowledge and technology to improve, inform and support a portfolio of projects, services, and initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about the role please refer to the attached Job Description &amp; Specifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Viki Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Business Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:Viki.smith@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
